                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Mike lead the direction and shaping of the Rewatch visual identity. Taking it from it's initial state, as a developer-focused brand, to a more universal look that could capture the interest of folks positioned across various roles in an organization. 
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        To propose and make directional decisions required Mike to have a deep understanding of both the product and customer. So, Mike worked closely with everyone. Through the product, Mike stayed informed on the newest insights that the sales and success teams were cultivating. Mike's manager, the Head of Design, primarily focused on the design of the product itself and was always helping Mike understand where the product was headed.
